Class Server

java.lang.Object
Server
Direct Known Subclasses:
SelfCheck
public class Server extends Object
A Server class that makes immutable Server objects containing an identifier, the time stamp of the Server's next available time, the maximum queue size, the current number of customers waiting in queue, the current availability of the Server, a supplied value for the Server's restTime, and an indicator to determine if the Server is a Human Server or a Self-Checkout.

      public Server(int serverId, double nextFree, int qmax, int serverQ, boolean avail, Supplier<Double> restTime, boolean self)
      Constructs a Server with all parameters specified.
      Parameters:
      serverId - the integer id of the server
      nextFree - the server's next free time
      qmax - the max queue size for the server
      serverQ - the integer value of the size of the server queue
      avail - the boolean availability of the server
      restTime - the server's restTime supplier.
      self - the boolean representation of self-checkout

    • canServe

      public boolean canServe(double time)
      Checks if server can serve at a given time. Returns true if the server is available and the server's next free time is greater than or equal to the given time.
      Parameters:
      time - the input timestamp to be checked.
      Returns:
      true if the server can serve.

    • updateServerState

      returns an updated Server.

    • minusOneServerQ

      public Server minusOneServerQ()
      Decrement the server queue by one. Invokes the private setServerQ method and subtracts 1 from the server queue.

      returns a Server with a queue decremented by 1.

    • addRestTime

      public Server addRestTime()
      Adds rest time to the server's next free time. Invokes the updateServerState method with the server's current next free time and the server's rest time generated from Supplier<Double> restTime.
      Returns:
      returns a Server with an updated next free time.
